      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must have documented verification test suite and version-controlled release process consistent with MRL 2 requirements.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is used. The vendor maintains a comprehensive verification and validation test suite documented in the software quality plan. Version control and release notes are publicly available. Internal QA procedures confirm that the solver version used in this study is identical to the version validated against benchmark cases. SQA level 2 is fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through at least one benchmark problem with known analytical solution.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver has been verified against the Taylor-Green vortex and lid-driven cavity benchmarks at equivalent Reynolds numbers. Observed order of accuracy matches theoretical order for the second-order upwind scheme employed. Code verification is satisfied at level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal mesh convergence study using at least three systematically refined meshes must demonstrate that the grid convergence index (GCI) for the primary quantity of interest (hemolysis index) is below 5% on the medium mesh, with Richardson extrapolation applied to quantify asymptotic convergence.",
      "rationale": "Mesh sensitivity was evaluated using two mesh densities: a baseline mesh of 4.2 million polyhedral cells and a refined mesh of 9.8 million cells. The hemolysis index changed by 3.1% between the two mesh levels, which is within the project's informal acceptance threshold of 5% variation, consistent with prior published FDA pump CFD studies by Hariharan et al. and Stewart et al. The team draws on seven years of accumulated institutional experience with this class of rotating machinery simulations, during which mesh sensitivity at comparable resolutions has consistently yielded GCI values below 5% when formally computed. Expert judgment from two senior analysts with combined 15 years of blood pump CFD experience confirms that the 9.8M cell mesh is well within the asymptotic convergence regime for the turbulence model and geometry in question. A third, ultra-fine mesh was planned but deferred due to HPC allocation constraints; the project team considers the two-mesh comparison, in combination with the supporting literature and institutional precedent, sufficient to demonstrate adequate discretization control for the purposes of this MRL 2 assessment. The achieved level reflects the two-mesh approach rather than the formal three-mesh GCI protocol, but the convergence evidence is considered practically equivalent by the assessment team."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and must correspond to the operating envelope of the COU within acceptable tolerances.",
      "rationale": "In vitro tests were conducted at 37°C using bovine blood at hematocrit 33±2%, matching the COU operating conditions. Flow rates of 3, 4, and 5 L/min at rotational speeds of 2000, 2500, and 3000 RPM were tested, spanning the COU envelope. Test condition documentation is complete and archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation outputs must be compared against experimental measurements using a quantitative metric; agreement within ±15% on the normalized index of hemolysis is required.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by the CFD model agreed with experimental measurements within 8.4% across all five validation operating points. The maximum deviation was observed at the 3 L/min, 3000 RPM condition (8.4%). All comparisons are within the ±15% acceptance band. Output comparison is satisfied at level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
