      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged scalar shear stress and exposure time distributions, which are mechanistically linked to RBC damage. Relevance is well-established in the blood pump CFD literature and confirmed by FDA guidance documents."
    },
